d [[Lviv]] (further to [[Kiev]]).\n\nUzhhorod is served by [[Uzhhorod International Airport]].\n\n==Sport==\nThe city was home to the [[SC Rusj Uzhorod]] football club from 1925. Contemporary side [[FC Hoverla Uzhhorod]] made their debut in the [[Ukrainian Premier League]] in 2001.\n\n==International relations==\n\n===Twin towns \u2013 Sister cities===\n{{See also|List of twin towns and sister cities in Ukraine}}\n\nUzhhorod is currently [[Twin towns and sister cities|twinned]] with:\n{{div col|colwidth=22em}}\n*{{flagicon|HUN}} [[B\u00e9k\u00e9scsaba]], Hungary\n*{{flagicon|HUN}} [[Ny\u00edregyh\u00e1za]], Hungary\n*{{flagicon|HUN}} [[Szombathely]], Hungary\n*{{flagicon|CRO}} [[Trogir]], [[Croatia]]\n*{{flagicon|CRO}} [[Pula]], Croatia\n*{{flagicon|USA}} [[Corvallis, Oregon|Corvallis]], [[Oregon]], [[United States|US]]\n*{{flagicon|GER}} [[Darmstadt]], Germany, since 1992<ref name=\"Darmstadt twinnings\">{{cite web|url=http://www.darmstadt.de/standort/staedtepartnerschaften-und-internationales/index.htm|title=St\u00e4dtepartnerschaften und Internationales|accessdate=26 July 2013|work=B\u00fcro f\u00fcr St\u00e4dtepartnerschaften und internationale Beziehungen|language = German}}</ref>\n*{{flagicon|SVK}} [[Ko\u0161ice]], [[Slovakia]], since 1993<ref name=\"Ko\u0161ice twinnings\">{{cite web|url=http://www.kosice.sk/clanok.php?file=gov_s_c-00_uk.html|title=Twin cities of the City of Kosice|accessdate=27 July 2013|work=Magistr\u00e1t mesta Ko\u0161ice, Tr.}}</ref>\n*{{flagicon|POL}} [[Krosno]], [[Poland]], since 2008<ref name=\"Twin\">''{{cite web|url=http://www.krosno.pl/?node=30|title=Krosno Official Website \u2013 Partner Cities|language=Polish|publisher=Urz\u0105d Miasta Krosna|accessdate=23 October 2008}}''</ref>\n*{{flagicon|POL}} [[Jaros\u0142aw]], [[Poland]], since 2002<ref name=\"Twin2\">''{{cite web|url=http://www.jaroslaw.pl/miasta-partnerskie|title=Jaros\u0142aw Official Website \u2013 Partner Cities|language=Polish|publisher=Urz\u0105d Miasta Jaros\u0142aw. Ul. Rynek 1, 37\u2013500 Jaros\u0142aw|accessdate=23 October 2008}}''</ref>\n*{{flagicon|CZE}} [[\u010cesk\u00e1 L\u00edpa]], Czech Republic\n*{{flagicon|ROU}} [[Satu Mare]], [[Romania]]<ref name=\"Uzhhorod-Satu Mare\">{{cite web|url=http://www.satu-mare.ro/evenimente/2006/12/04/ProtocolDeColaborareUjgorod-SatuMare.html|title=Protocol de colaborare Ujgorod-Satu Mare|publisher=www.satu-mare.ro|language=Romanian|accessdate=27 June 2009}}</ref>\n{{colend}}\n\n==Notable residents==\n* [[Vladimir Koman]], a [[Ukrainian people|Ukrainian]]-born, [[Hungarian people|Hungarian]] [[Association football|football]] player\n* [[J\u00e1nos Erd\u00e9lyi]], a [[Hungarian people|Hungarian]] poet, critic, author, philosopher and ethnographist\n* [[Shlomo Ganzfried]], an [[Orthodox Judaism|Orthodox]] [[rabbi]] and [[posek]]\n* [[J\u00f3zef Kasparek]], a [[Poland|Polish]] lawyer, historian and [[political scientist]]\n* [[Mikhail Kopelman]], a violinist\n* [[Joseph L. Kun]], emigrated to the United States, became a judge\n* [[Samuel Lipsch\u00fctz]], a [[chess]] player and author\n* [[Lika Roman]],  [[Miss Ukraine]] 2007\n* [[Yozhef Sabo]], a [[Soviet Union|Soviet]] [[Association football|football]] player of Hungarian ethnicity\n* [[Avhustyn Voloshyn]], a [[Outer Subcarpathia|Subcarpathia]]n politician, teacher, and essayist\n* [[Anatoly Zatin]], a composer, pianist and conductor\n* [[Gregory Zatkovich]], first governor of [[Carpathian Ruthenia]]\n* [[Andriy Zayats]], diplomat, State Secretary\n\n==Gallery==\n<gallery mode=\"packed\"   heights=\"160px\" >\nFile:21-101-0002 Uzhgorod Exaltation Cathedral RB.jpg|Cathedral of the Exaltation of the Holy Cross\nFile:UzhhorodBridge2.jpg|Pedestrian Bridge across Uzh River, between [[Pet\u00f6fi]] Square and Teatralna Square\nFile:Uzhhorod2017-2.jpg|Tourist street signs in Uzhhorod\nFile:\u041a\u043e\u043c\u043f\u043b\u0435\u043a\u0441 \u0417\u0430\u043c\u043a\u043e\u0432\u043e\u0457 \u0433\u043e\u0440\u0438003.JPG|Lamplighter statue in Uzhhorod\nFile:Aerial view Uzhhorod -Amphitheatre-0308.jpg|Aerial view of Uzhhorod - Amphitheatre and residential neighborhood.\nFile:\u041c\u0456\u043d\u0456-\u0441\u043a\u0443\u043b\u044c\u043f\u0442\u0443\u0440\u0430 \u0406\u0448\u0442\u0432\u0430\u043d\u0430 \u041b\u0430\u0443\u0434\u043e\u043d\u0430.jpg|Mini-sculpture in Hospital Square Garden\nFile:21-101-0044 Uzgorod02.jpg|Residential street\nFile:\u0412\u0438\u0445\u0456\u0434 \u0437 \u0422\u0435\u0430\u0442\u0440\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u043e\u0457 \u043f\u043b\u043e\u0449\u0456 \u043d\u0430 \u0432\u0443\u043b. \u041a\u043e\u0440\u0437\u043e.jpg|Korzo Street in the Historical center of Uzhhorod\nFile:Uzhorod Teatralna 5-4.jpg|Teatralna Square\nFile:Uzhhorod River Uzh 1.JPG|thumbnail|[[Uzh River]]\nFile:\u0428\u0435\u043b\u0435\u0441\u0442\u0456\u0432\u0441\u044c\u043a\u0430 \u041c\u0438\u0445\u0430\u0439-\u043b\u0456\u0432\u0441\u044c\u043a\u0430 \u0446\u0435\u0440\u043a\u0432\u0430 2.jpg|thumb|150px|Wooden Greek-Catholic church (1777) in the [[Museum of Folk Architecture and Life, Uzhhorod|Museum of Folk Architecture.]]\n</gallery>\n\n==See also==\n*[[Bridges in Uzhhorod]]\n*[[Uzhgorod Synagogue]]\n*[[Zakarpattia Oblast]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|colwidth=30em}}\n\n== Further reading ==\n* Rampley, Matthew (2019). \"Uzhhorod Modernism\" (2019). https://craace.com/2019/05/09/uzhhorod-modernism/\n*{{Cite journal|ref=harv|last=V\u00e9ghse\u0151|first=Tam\u00e1s|title=Reflections on the Background to the Union of Uzhhorod / Ungv\u00e1r (1646)|journal=Eastern Theological Journal|year=2015|volume=1|issue=1|pages=147\u2013181|url=http://real.mtak.hu/39976/3/veghseo_ETJ_1_2015.pdf}}\n\n==External links==\n{{sisterlinks|Uzhhorod|voy=Uzhhorod}}\n* [https://rada-uzhgorod.gov.ua/ Official website of the City\n* [http://www.uzhnuedu.com/ Official website of Uzhhorod National University]\n* [http://ungvar.vox.com.ua/ Uzhhorod in old postcards]\n*[http://am.umodernism.com/en/ Uzhhorod Modernism Architectural Manual]\n\n{